		"Details": "Developed as a prototype by the CCAF for a static defense 'Mech used to defend critical locations in the Confederation, The Anvil was eventually discarded as being impractical. However, Solaris VII loves impractical designs and so adopted the design as an arena fighter. Built on a 300-rated Light Fusion Engine, The Anvil is designed around twin Long Tom Artillery Cannons, giving it tremendous firepower against any enemy. Unfortunately, the bulk of the cannons prevents the mounting of any backup weaponry, so The Anvil relies on its Laser AMS for sole defense if the cannons run dry. Still, the cannons hit so hard that very little endures against The Anvil.",
